Doris BARKSCHAT, Appellant, v. Frank CHICHESTER, Trustee in Bankruptcy of the Estate of Henry Barkschat, Bankrupt, Appellee. No. 8986. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Feb. 17, 1939. Rex B. Goodcell, Manley C. Davidson, and Bertram H. Ross, all of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellant. Ignatius F. Parker, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before DENMAN, MATHEWS, and HEALY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon consideration of the record and briefs, and after oral arguments of counsel, ordered order of District Court reversed, that a decree be filed and entered accordingly, and the mandate of this court issue as provided in Rule 28.
